    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small wine glasses of distinctive shape and size, designed for drinking sherry, a fortified wine of Spanish origin. Sherry glasses have a round foot, a stem, and small bowl; a common design has a tapering bowl that is colored at the lip and fades to a light color or clear at the top of the stem. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
